  "prompt": "How much percentage of inorganic organic and water present in enamel cementum and dentine?",
  "response": "Here's a breakdown of the composition of tooth tissues:\n\nEnamel:\n\u2022 Inorganic (hydroxyapatite crystals): 96-97%\n\u2022 Organic material: 1-2%\n\u2022 Water: 2-3%\n\nDentin:\n\u2022 Inorganic: 70%\n\u2022 Organic material: 20%\n\u2022 Water: 10%\n\nCementum:\n\u2022 Inorganic: 45-50%\n\u2022 Organic material: 50-55%\n\u2022 Water: Approximately 5-10%\n\nThese percentages can vary slightly depending on the specific source and individual variations, but the general proportions remain consistent across most dental literature.\n\nThe composition reflects the different functional roles of each tooth tissue:\n- Enamel: Highly mineralized for protection\n- Dentin: More flexible, provides support\n- Cementum: Helps attach tooth to periodontal ligament\n\nThe high mineral content in enamel provides its characteristic hardness and resistance to wear, while the higher organic content in dentin and cementum allows for more flexibility and biological adaptation.",
